ğŸ§  How Attackers Recover Weak Passwords

They donâ€™t break encryption â€” they guess passwords.

Dictionary attacks: try known/common passwords (rockyou, leaks).

Mask attacks: brute-force with patterns (e.g., ?l?l?l?d?d).

GPU cracking: massively speeds up attacks.

Detection: high GPU usage, cracking tools executed, wordlists accessed.



ğŸ“„ 2. PDF cracking
pdfcrack (dictionary attack)
pdfcrack -f flag.pdf -w /usr/share/wordlists/rockyou.txt

John (via pdf2john)
pdf2john.pl flag.pdf > pdfhash.txt
john --wordlist=/usr/share/wordlists/rockyou.txt pdfhash.txt

ğŸ—œ 3. ZIP cracking
