john --wordlist=/usr/share/wordlists/rockyou.txt ziphash.txt

fcrackzip
fcrackzip -u -D -p /usr/share/wordlists/rockyou.txt flag.zip

ğŸ¯ 4. Mask / brute-force (example patterns)

Format example:
?l?l?l?d?d â†’ 3 lowercase + 2 digits
(used by hashcat / john incremental)

Hashcat example mask:
hashcat -a 3 -m <hashmode> hash.txt ?l?l?l?d?d

ğŸ•µï¸ Detection Indicators (very short)

Processes: john, hashcat, fcrackzip, pdfcrack, zip2john, pdf2john.pl.

CLI flags: --wordlist, -w, --mask, -a 3, rockyou.txt.

Files touched: john.pot, .hashcat/hashcat.potfile.

GPU spikes: nvidia-smi showing hashcat/john.

ğŸ›¡ Response Playbook (minimal)

Isolate host

Collect artifacts (process list, GPU stats, wordlists, hashes)

Preserve working directory + history

Check what was decrypted

Verify if authorized

Rotate credentials + enforce MFA
